<Layout title="EN: Overview">
  <h1>A non-incremental path for Latin America</h1>
  <p class="lead">
    Futuros is a regional blueprint for Latin America to lead ethical and inclusive technological transformation
    by 2035, using AI and frontier technologies as systemic accelerators — not isolated tools — to break the
    structural trap of low growth and high inequality.
  </p>

  <h2>By 2035</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Productivity growth of 1.9–2.3% annually (vs. 0.6% historical).</li>
    <li>USD 1.1–1.7 trillion of additional cumulative economic value.</li>
    <li>60% of critical compute under regional jurisdiction.</li>
    <li>15M new formal jobs in Futuros-aligned sectors.</li>
    <li>Region as exporter of ethical, regionally-tailored AI solutions.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Three non-negotiable bets</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Locally grounded</strong>: models in Spanish, Portuguese, and 8+ indigenous languages with parity performance.</li>
    <li><strong>Inclusive and ethical by design</strong>: binding gap-closing KPIs, not aspirational. Mandatory algorithmic auditing.</li>
    <li><strong>Explicit leapfrogging</strong>: skipping stages — mobile-first finance, preventive health via wearables, distributed renewable grids.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Implementation phases</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Phase</th><th>Years</th><th>Goal</th><th>Investment</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Demonstration</td><td>2026–2028</td><td>8 cross-country pilots + institutional design</td><td>USD 2–3 bn</td></tr>
      <tr><td>National scaling</td><td>2029–2032</td><td>Mass adoption + regional commons operating</td><td>USD 8–12 bn</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Transformation</td><td>2033–2035</td><td>Consolidation + export</td><td>USD 5–8 bn</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

